# P02 — slope physics smoke test.
#
# level_build_tutorial has a temporary slope test bed at floor-row mid-map:
#   - 45° slope at x=1500..1628 (hypotenuse from upper-left to lower-right)
#   - 60° slope at x=1700..1774
#   - 5°  slope at x=1850..1987
#
# This script lands the player above the 60° slope. Headline test:
# without any input, the mech should slide downhill (slope friction
# 0.955 isn't enough to overcome gravity-along-tangent at 60°).
#
# Tick layout:
#   60   — landed on slope, no input yet
#   180  — passive slide ~2s in (compare pelvis x to t=60)
#   240  — kicked input RIGHT (running downhill) — tangent-projected
#          velocity should outpace passive slide
#   300  — release; observe coast then settle
#
# A "settled" mech without input that slid downhill noticeably between
# t=60 and t=180 confirms the slope physics path is alive end-to-end:
# slope-aware friction + slope-tangent velocity + slope-aware anchor
# all firing.

window 1280 720
seed 1 0
out build/shots
spawn_at 1740 800
aim 1840 1000

# Land + passive slide.
at 60  shot landed_t060
at 120 shot slide_t120
at 180 shot slide_t180

# Run downhill (right).
at 200 press right
at 240 shot running_t240

# Coast.
at 270 release right
at 360 shot settled_t360

contact_sheet sheet cols 5

at 420 end
